---
import FridayHarborLayout from '../../layouts/FridayHarborLayout.astro';
import { entries } from '../../data/friday-harbor';
const entry = entries.find(e => e.slug === '2026-04-26-where-the-cloud-touches-ground')!;
---
<FridayHarborLayout entry={entry}>
  <figure slot="figure" class="cloud-figure">
    <div class="cloud-stage" id="stage" aria-label="Map of US AI data center clusters">
      <p class="map-status">
        <span data-lang="en">Loading map...</span>
        <span data-lang="zh">地图加载中...</span>
      </p>
    </div>

    <figcaption data-lang="en">
      <b>The cloud is a geography.</b>
      Most of the AI we use travels through these eleven dots before it reaches a screen.
      Loudoun County, Virginia carries an estimated 70&nbsp;% of global internet traffic.
      Around it — Phoenix, Dallas, Hillsboro, Quincy, Des Moines, New Albany — each a quiet
      American county that has become a planetary node. Circle area approximates operating
      capacity (MW); the warm wash across the West is the rough footprint of long-term water stress.
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-cloud-major"></span>
        <span><b>Loudoun County, VA</b> — Data Center Alley, the densest concentration on Earth.</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <figcaption data-lang="zh">
      <b>「云」是一种地理事实。</b>
      我们日常用的大多数 AI，到达屏幕之前都要经过这十一个点。
      位于弗吉尼亚州的 Loudoun 县据估承担着全球互联网约 70&nbsp;% 的流量。
      它的周围——凤凰城、达拉斯、希尔斯伯勒、昆西、得梅因、新奥尔巴尼——每一个
      都是表面安静、实际是行星级节点的美国县。圆点面积近似运行容量（MW）；
      西部那层暖色铺底，是长期水资源紧张的大致地理范围。
      <span class="legend-line">
        <span class="legend-swatch swatch-cloud-major"></span>
        <span><b>弗吉尼亚 Loudoun 县</b>——Data Center Alley，地球上最密集的算力聚集点。</span>
      </span>
    </figcaption>

    <aside class="cloud-stats" aria-label="key US data-center figures">
      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 250<small>&nbsp;TWh / yr</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">US data-centre electricity (≈ 4&nbsp;% of national grid)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 2,500<small>&nbsp;亿 kWh / 年</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">美国数据中心年耗电（约占全国电网 4&nbsp;%）</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 660<small>&nbsp;B gal / yr</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">water for cooling, mostly in already-stressed basins</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 6,600<small>&nbsp;亿加仑 / 年</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">冷却用水，多数取自已紧张的流域</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 70<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">of global internet traffic transits Loudoun County</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 70<small>&nbsp;%</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">全球互联网流量经 Loudoun 县中转</span>
      </div>

      <div class="stat" data-lang="en">
        <span class="stat-num">~ 3<small>&nbsp;×</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">projected growth in US data-centre power demand by 2030</span>
      </div>
      <div class="stat" data-lang="zh">
        <span class="stat-num">约 3<small>&nbsp;×</small></span>
        <span class="stat-label">美国数据中心电力需求至 2030 年预计增长</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </figure>

  <div slot="notebook-en">
    <p>
      "The cloud" is the most successful piece of evasive language of our era.
      Every time someone says <em>send it to the cloud</em>, a specific concrete building
      somewhere in a specific American county receives the bytes, runs them across silicon,
      and sends them back. The cloud is geography — it just isn't a geography most of us are
      ever asked to look at.
    </p>
    <p>
      That geography is concentrated, and concentrated by design. Counties get chosen for
      their tax breaks, their cheap electricity, their proximity to the fiber backbones laid
      down in the 1990s. Loudoun County, Virginia, is denser than the rest by an order of
      magnitude: its data centers carry roughly seventy percent of global internet traffic.
      Around it, a handful of secondary clusters: Phoenix, Dallas, Hillsboro, Quincy,
      Des Moines, New Albany. Together they consume an amount of electricity that would, on
      its own, rank around the twenty-fifth-largest country in the world.
    </p>
    <p>
      The bill comes due locally. Phoenix data centers compete with cities for the dwindling
      Colorado River. Loudoun residents have been in transmission-line battles with their
      utility for two years. Ohio farmers near New Albany lost row crops to Intel's
      semiconductor expansion and the data centers it pulled in. The job a map can do here
      is small but specific: take the per-prompt water number that floats around in articles
      and put it back where it actually lands — on a county, in a basin, beside a transformer.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI demand is going to make this harder. Generative models have already pushed the
      annual power-demand growth curve away from a flat plateau and onto a near-vertical
      line. The map you're looking at is a 2026 snapshot; in three years it will need to
      grow about three times as many dots, and many of those will land on the same handful
      of counties — because once the substation is built and the fiber is in, the next
      tenant comes for the same reasons.
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>A small disclosure.</em> Capacity figures are illustrative. Operators rarely
      publish exact numbers; the values plotted here are reconstructed from public filings,
      news coverage, and industry reports. Locations are accurate to within the metropolitan
      area. The water-stress wash across the western states is a sketched climatological
      footprint, not a hydrological dataset.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div slot="notebook-zh">
    <p>
      「云」是这一代最成功的回避词。每次有人说「放到云里就行」，地球上某个具体县的
      某栋具体建筑就接收了那串字节，让它们在硅上跑一遍，再发回来。云是地理——
      只是大多数人从来没被邀请看一眼那张图。
    </p>
    <p>
      这片地理是高度集中的，而且是有意为之。一个县被选中，是因为它有税收减免、
      电力便宜、紧贴 1990 年代铺下的光纤主干。其中弗吉尼亚州的 Loudoun 县密度
      比其他所有地方高一个数量级：这里的数据中心承载了大约百分之七十的全球
      互联网流量。围绕 Loudoun，还有几个二级集群：凤凰城、达拉斯、希尔斯伯勒、
      昆西、得梅因、新奥尔巴尼。这些集群一起消耗的电量，单算下来能在世界国家
      排名里挤进前二十五。
    </p>
    <p>
      代价是地方承担的。凤凰城的数据中心在和市民争夺日益干涸的科罗拉多河水。
      Loudoun 县居民已经和电力公司打了两年的输电线官司。俄亥俄新奥尔巴尼的
      农民为了让 Intel 半导体扩建工厂、以及随之而来的数据中心，失去了大片
      庄稼地。一张地图能做的事很小但很具体：把那个偶尔被引用的「ChatGPT
      每条提问耗水多少毫升」的数字，重新放回它真实的落地处——某个县、
      某条流域、某座变电站旁边。
    </p>
    <p>
      AI 需求会让这件事更难。生成式模型已经把年电力需求增长曲线从一条平的
      高原推上了几乎直立的斜线。你现在看的这张图是 2026 年的快照；三年之后
      它需要长出大约三倍的点，而其中很多还会落在这几十个相同的县——
      因为一旦变电站和光纤已经铺好了，下一家进驻者也是看重了同样的理由。
    </p>
    <p class="aside">
      <em>附注：</em>容量数据为示意性数字。运营方很少公开精确容量；图中数值
      由公开备案文件、新闻报道与行业报告反推。地理位置精确到大都市区。
      西部各州那层水资源紧张的暖色铺底，是大致的气候带勾勒，不是水文数据。
    </p>
  </div>

  <ul slot="provenance-en">
    <li>US states geometry: <a href="https://github.com/topojson/us-atlas" rel="noopener"><code>us-atlas@3 states-10m</code></a> via jsDelivr.</li>
    <li>Cluster locations and approximate capacity: cross-referenced from <a href="https://www.datacentermap.com/" rel="noopener">DataCenterMap</a>, county-level filings (Loudoun BOS, Maricopa, Dallas-Fort Worth COG), and 2024–2025 trade-press coverage. Hyperscaler operators rarely publish exact MW figures; values are reconstructed.</li>
    <li>Loudoun County share of internet traffic: industry estimate cited by the Northern Virginia Technology Council; the 60–70 % range is commonly reported.</li>
    <li>US data-centre electricity: <a href="https://www.energy.gov/eere/buildings/articles/energy-efficiency-data-centers" rel="noopener">DOE 2024</a> and <a href="https://www.iea.org/reports/electricity-2024" rel="noopener">IEA Electricity 2024</a>; ≈ 250 TWh, ≈ 4 % of US grid.</li>
    <li>Water consumption: <a href="https://www.osti.gov/biblio/2476988" rel="noopener">Lawrence Berkeley National Laboratory, 2024 Data Center Energy Report</a>; 660 B gallons/year is direct + indirect.</li>
    <li>2030 growth projection: McKinsey Global Energy Perspective 2024 / IEA Electricity 2024.</li>
    <li>Source map &amp; build script: <code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-26-where-the-cloud-touches-ground.astro</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <ul slot="provenance-zh">
    <li>美国州界几何：<a href="https://github.com/topojson/us-atlas" rel="noopener"><code>us-atlas@3 states-10m</code></a>，经 jsDelivr 加载。</li>
    <li>集群位置与近似容量：综合 <a href="https://www.datacentermap.com/" rel="noopener">DataCenterMap</a>、县级公开备案（Loudoun 县议会、Maricopa 县、达拉斯-沃斯堡 COG）以及 2024–2025 行业报道反推。运营方很少披露精确 MW 数据。</li>
    <li>Loudoun 县互联网流量占比：行业估算，常引区间为 60–70 %（北弗吉尼亚科技委员会等机构）。</li>
    <li>美国数据中心年耗电：<a href="https://www.energy.gov/eere/buildings/articles/energy-efficiency-data-centers" rel="noopener">美国能源部 2024</a> 与 <a href="https://www.iea.org/reports/electricity-2024" rel="noopener">IEA Electricity 2024</a>；约 2,500 亿 kWh，约占全国电网 4 %。</li>
    <li>用水量：<a href="https://www.osti.gov/biblio/2476988" rel="noopener">劳伦斯伯克利国家实验室 2024 数据中心能耗报告</a>；6,600 亿加仑为直接 + 间接。</li>
    <li>至 2030 年增长预测：McKinsey Global Energy Perspective 2024 / IEA Electricity 2024。</li>
    <li>源码与构建脚本：<code>src/pages/friday-harbor/2026-04-26-where-the-cloud-touches-ground.astro</code>。</li>
  </ul>
</FridayHarborLayout>

<style>
  .cloud-figure { margin: 0; }
  .cloud-stage {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    background: transparent;
    border: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
  }
  .cloud-stage svg { display: block; width: 100%; height: 100%; }
  .map-status {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .cloud-figure figcaption {
    margin: 1.1rem 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    font-family: var(--serif);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 880px;
  }
  .cloud-figure figcaption b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  .cloud-figure figcaption em { color: var(--uw-purple-deep); font-style: italic; }
  .cloud-figure figcaption .legend-line {
    display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .cloud-figure figcaption .legend-swatch {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: 14px; height: 14px;
    margin-top: 4px;
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .swatch-cloud-major {
    background: #8a3e2e;
    border: 2px solid var(--rose);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(194,160,148,0.32);
  }
  .aside {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--rule);
    padding-left: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    font-size: 0.88rem !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Hard-numbers strip — same pattern as the Hormuz entry. */
  .cloud-stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin: 1.4rem 0.2rem 0;
    padding: 1rem 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .cloud-stats .stat {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }
  .cloud-stats .stat-num {
    font-family: var(--display, "Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 1.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--uw-purple-deep);
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums lining-nums;
  }
  .cloud-stats .stat-num small {
    font-size: 0.55em;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-left: 0.1em;
  }
  .cloud-stats .stat-label {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 14em;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .cloud-stats { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 1rem; }
  }
</style>

<script type="module">
  import * as d3 from 'https://esm.sh/d3@7';
  import { feature } from 'https://esm.sh/topojson-client@3';

  // Major US AI / hyperscaler data center clusters.
  // Capacity (MW) is illustrative — operators rarely publish exact figures.
  const CLUSTERS = [
    { id: 'loudoun', name: { en: 'Loudoun Co., VA',   zh: 'Loudoun 县' },        lon: -77.55,  lat: 39.05, cap: 3500, anchor: true,  side: 'right' },
    { id: 'phoenix', name: { en: 'Phoenix metro',     zh: '凤凰城' },             lon: -111.95, lat: 33.45, cap: 1200, side: 'right' },
    { id: 'dfw',     name: { en: 'Dallas–Fort Worth', zh: '达拉斯' },             lon: -96.80,  lat: 32.78, cap: 1500, side: 'right' },
    { id: 'atl',     name: { en: 'Atlanta',           zh: '亚特兰大' },           lon: -84.39,  lat: 33.75, cap: 800,  side: 'right' },
    { id: 'chi',     name: { en: 'Chicago',           zh: '芝加哥' },             lon: -87.65,  lat: 41.85, cap: 600,  side: 'left'  },
    { id: 'iowa',    name: { en: 'Des Moines, IA',    zh: '得梅因' },             lon: -93.62,  lat: 41.59, cap: 700,  side: 'left'  },
    { id: 'ohio',    name: { en: 'New Albany, OH',    zh: '新奥尔巴尼' },         lon: -82.81,  lat: 40.08, cap: 400,  side: 'left'  },
    { id: 'pdx',     name: { en: 'Hillsboro, OR',     zh: '希尔斯伯勒' },         lon: -122.99, lat: 45.52, cap: 600,  side: 'left'  },
    { id: 'wa',      name: { en: 'Quincy, WA',        zh: '昆西' },               lon: -119.85, lat: 47.23, cap: 700,  side: 'right' },
    { id: 'reno',    name: { en: 'Reno, NV',          zh: '里诺' },               lon: -119.81, lat: 39.53, cap: 600,  side: 'left'  },
    { id: 'slc',     name: { en: 'Salt Lake City',    zh: '盐湖城' },             lon: -111.89, lat: 40.76, cap: 300,  side: 'right' }
  ];

  const css = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement);
  const c = {
    paper:   css.getPropertyValue('--bg-card').trim()   || '#f5efe2',
    paper2:  css.getPropertyValue('--bg-deep').trim()   || '#ddd4c2',
    rule:    css.getPropertyValue('--rule').trim()      || '#d6cdbf',
    ink:     css.getPropertyValue('--ink').trim()       || '#2c2823',
    inkSoft: css.getPropertyValue('--ink-soft').trim()  || '#6c6358',
    inkFaint:css.getPropertyValue('--ink-faint').trim() || '#98907f',
    purple:  css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple').trim() || '#6a5a6e',
    purpleD: css.getPropertyValue('--uw-purple-deep').trim() || '#4a3e4d',
    sage:    css.getPropertyValue('--sage').trim()      || '#8e9c8a',
    sageS:   css.getPropertyValue('--sage-soft').trim() || '#b4bdaf',
    rose:    css.getPropertyValue('--rose').trim()      || '#c2a094',
    mist:    css.getPropertyValue('--mist').trim()      || '#a8b1b3',
  };
  const EVENT_DEEP = '#8a3e2e';

  let _states = null;
  fetch('https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/us-atlas@3/states-10m.json')
    .then(r => r.json())
    .then(us => {
      _states = feature(us, us.objects.states);
      requestAnimationFrame(() => draw());
    });

  window.addEventListener('resize', () => { if (_states) draw(); });

  const fhRoot = document.querySelector('.fh-root');
  if (fhRoot) {
    new MutationObserver(() => { if (_states) draw(); })
      .observe(fhRoot, { attributes: true, attributeFilter: ['data-lang'] });
  }
  function currentLang() {
    return fhRoot && fhRoot.getAttribute('data-lang') === 'zh' ? 'zh' : 'en';
  }

  function draw() {
    const states = _states;
    if (!states) return;
    const stage = document.getElementById('stage');
    if (!stage) return;
    const W = stage.clientWidth | 0;
    const H = stage.clientHeight | 0;
    if (W < 50 || H < 50) { requestAnimationFrame(() => draw()); return; }
    stage.innerHTML = '';

    const lang = currentLang();
    const padL = 14, padR = 14, padT = 16, padB = 60;
    const mapW = W - padL - padR;
    const mapH = H - padT - padB;

    const projection = d3.geoAlbersUsa()
      .fitSize([mapW, mapH], states)
      .translate([padL + mapW / 2, padT + mapH / 2]);
    const path = d3.geoPath(projection);

    const svg = d3.select(stage).append('svg')
      .attr('viewBox', `0 0 ${W} ${H}`)
      .attr('width', W).attr('height', H)
      .style('display', 'block')
      .style('overflow', 'hidden');

    // Background paper
    svg.append('rect').attr('width', W).attr('height', H).attr('fill', c.paper);

    // ----- Aridity wash (peaks over the Southwest, fades east) -----
    const aridGradId = 'fh-cloud-arid';
    const aridGrad = svg.append('defs').append('linearGradient').attr('id', aridGradId)
      .attr('gradientUnits', 'userSpaceOnUse')
      .attr('x1', padL).attr('y1', 0).attr('x2', padL + mapW).attr('y2', 0);
    aridGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '0%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.18);
    aridGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '22%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.55);
    aridGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '40%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.32);
    aridGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '60%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.10);
    aridGrad.append('stop').attr('offset', '85%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.0);

    // States base — warm putty
    svg.append('path').datum(states).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', c.paper2).attr('stroke', 'none');

    // Aridity overlay clipped to land
    svg.append('path').datum(states).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', `url(#${aridGradId})`).attr('stroke', 'none');

    // State borders
    svg.append('path').datum(states).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.40)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.5);
    // National outline (slightly heavier)
    const nation = { type: 'GeometryCollection', geometries: states.features.map(f => f.geometry) };
    svg.append('path').datum(states).attr('d', path)
      .attr('fill', 'none')
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.85)
      .attr('stroke-width', 0.8)
      .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');

    // ----- "Arid Southwest" floating label -----
    const aridLabel = lang === 'zh' ? '干旱的西南' : 'Arid Southwest';
    const aridP = projection([-110, 36]);
    if (aridP) {
      const t = svg.append('text').attr('x', aridP[0]).attr('y', aridP[1])
        .attr('fill', c.purpleD).attr('fill-opacity', 0.55)
        .attr('font-style', 'italic')
        .attr('font-family', lang === 'zh'
          ? '"Noto Serif SC", "Songti SC", serif'
          : '"Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif')
        .attr('font-size', 14).attr('letter-spacing', '0.30em')
        .attr('text-anchor', 'middle')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.85)').attr('stroke-width', 3)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round');
      t.text(aridLabel);
    }

    // ----- Cluster proportional symbols -----
    const maxCap = d3.max(CLUSTERS, d => d.cap);
    const rScale = d3.scaleSqrt().domain([0, maxCap]).range([0, 32]);

    // halos under everything
    const haloG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-cloud-halos');
    CLUSTERS.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const r = rScale(d.cap);
      haloG.append('circle').attr('cx', p[0]).attr('cy', p[1])
        .attr('r', r + 4).attr('fill', c.rose).attr('fill-opacity', 0.30);
    });

    // dots
    const dotG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-cloud-dots');
    CLUSTERS.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const r = rScale(d.cap);
      const g = dotG.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${p[0]},${p[1]})`);
      g.append('circle').attr('r', r).attr('fill', EVENT_DEEP).attr('fill-opacity', 0.78)
        .attr('stroke', c.paper).attr('stroke-width', 1.2);
      if (d.anchor) {
        // Loudoun gets an extra slow pulsing ring
        const outer = g.append('circle').attr('r', r + 8).attr('fill', 'none')
          .attr('stroke', EVENT_DEEP).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.55).attr('stroke-width', 1.5);
        outer.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'r')
          .attr('values', `${r + 6};${r + 16};${r + 6}`).attr('dur', '3.2s').attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
        outer.append('animate').attr('attributeName', 'stroke-opacity')
          .attr('values', '0.65;0.10;0.65').attr('dur', '3.2s').attr('repeatCount', 'indefinite');
      }
    });

    // labels — placed left or right of each dot per side hint
    const labelG = svg.append('g').attr('class', 'fh-cloud-labels');
    CLUSTERS.forEach(d => {
      const p = projection([d.lon, d.lat]);
      if (!p) return;
      const r = rScale(d.cap);
      const isRight = d.side !== 'left';
      const x = p[0] + (isRight ? r + 7 : -r - 7);
      const y = p[1] + 4;
      labelG.append('text')
        .attr('x', x).attr('y', y)
        .attr('text-anchor', isRight ? 'start' : 'end')
        .attr('fill', c.ink)
        .attr('font-size', d.anchor ? 13 : 11)
        .attr('font-weight', d.anchor ? 700 : 600)
        .attr('font-family', 'Inter, "Noto Sans CJK", sans-serif')
        .attr('paint-order', 'stroke')
        .attr('stroke', 'rgba(245,239,226,0.92)').attr('stroke-width', 3.5)
        .attr('stroke-linejoin', 'round')
        .text(d.name[lang]);
    });

    // ----- Capacity legend (bottom-left of map area) -----
    const legendCaps = [500, 1500, 3500];
    const legX = padL + 24;
    const legY = padT + mapH - 8;
    const legG = svg.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${legX},${legY})`);
    legG.append('text').attr('x', 0).attr('y', -54)
      .attr('font-size', 11).attr('fill', c.inkSoft)
      .attr('font-style', 'italic')
      .attr('font-family', lang === 'zh'
        ? '"Noto Serif SC", "Songti SC", serif'
        : '"Cormorant Garamond", Georgia, serif')
      .text(lang === 'zh' ? '估算运行容量（兆瓦）' : 'estimated capacity (MW)');
    legendCaps.forEach((cap, i) => {
      const r = rScale(cap);
      const x = i * 78;
      legG.append('circle').attr('cx', x).attr('cy', -22).attr('r', r)
        .attr('fill', 'none').attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-width', 0.9);
      legG.append('text').attr('x', x).attr('y', -22 + r + 14)
        .attr('text-anchor', 'middle').attr('font-size', 10)
        .attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif')
        .text(`${cap}`);
    });

    // ----- Aridity legend swatch -----
    const aridSwX = padL + mapW - 240;
    const aridSwY = padT + mapH - 28;
    const aridSwG = svg.append('g').attr('transform', `translate(${aridSwX},${aridSwY})`);
    const aridGradHX = 'fh-cloud-arid-h';
    const aridGradH = svg.append('defs').append('linearGradient').attr('id', aridGradHX)
      .attr('gradientUnits', 'objectBoundingBox')
      .attr('x1', 0).attr('y1', 0).attr('x2', 1).attr('y2', 0);
    aridGradH.append('stop').attr('offset', '0%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.78);
    aridGradH.append('stop').attr('offset', '100%').attr('stop-color', '#e6cf9c').attr('stop-opacity', 0.0);
    aridSwG.append('rect').attr('x', 0).attr('y', 0).attr('width', 100).attr('height', 12)
      .attr('fill', `url(#${aridGradHX})`)
      .attr('stroke', c.inkSoft).attr('stroke-opacity', 0.4).attr('stroke-width', 0.5);
    aridSwG.append('text').attr('x', 0).attr('y', 26)
      .attr('font-size', 9).attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif')
      .text(lang === 'zh' ? '紧张' : 'water-stressed');
    aridSwG.append('text').attr('x', 100).attr('y', 26)
      .attr('text-anchor', 'end')
      .attr('font-size', 9).attr('fill', c.inkSoft).attr('font-family', 'Inter, sans-serif')
      .text(lang === 'zh' ? '湿润' : 'humid');
  }
</script>
